      <h2>About</h2>

      <p>
        Noel Keyserman is a bilingual poet writing in English and Russian.
        His work explores memory, love, exile, music, irony, aging, and the
        fleeting moments that shape a life.
      </p>

      <p>
        <strong>Keyserman Press</strong> was created as an independent imprint
        for publishing bilingual literary work, poetry readings, and future
        Russian-English literary projects.
      </p>

      <p>
        Its first publication is <em>Moments / Моменты</em>, a bilingual
        collection of poems in English and Russian.
      </p>
